Citation.sAbstract: In this work, a thermophysical study of lactates compounds (methyl, ethyl and butyl lactate)  has been made to get an idea of the suitability of these chemicals in order to be considered as green.  New data about the physicochemical behaviour of these chemicals (density, refractive index, speed of  sound, viscosity, vapour pressure, static permittivity, surface tension and derived properties such as  molar refraction, isentropic compressibility and enthalpy of surface formation) have been measured  under atmospheric pressure at temperatures from 278.15 K to 228.15 K, while the vapour pressure  was determined over a temperature range from 303.15 K to 378.15K.
